  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD model employs a single-phase incompressible Newtonian blood rheology formulation; the known non-Newtonian shear-thinning behavior of blood at low shear rates is excluded from the model on the basis of an engineering judgment that shear rates in the pump impeller region are sufficiently high to render this effect negligible. No quantitative fidelity trade study comparing Newtonian versus non-Newtonian predictions was conducted, and the validation test matrix does not include low-flow operating points where shear-thinning effects would be most pronounced.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-worst-case-ident",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cfd-hemolysis-mrl2-accepted",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-newtonian-v2",
